Description: Rim and shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery dinos; interior: reserved at top, glazed streakily below; rim and outside slipped cream; edges of rim glazed, on top guilloche; at top of shoulder, between lines, frieze of tongues, some red, with spikes in the interstices; below animal frieze; from left, part of possible antler of goat, to right and part of goat's back; group of short vertical strokes and short zigzag as filling ornament.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Dimensions: Diameter: 20 - 25 centimetres (of rim, internal and external)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.04)
